To ensure your **QuantumEarn** platform is secure, you must apply these Firestore Security Rules in your Firebase Console. These rules prevent users from modifying their own balances, elevating their permissions to Admin, or accessing other users' private data.

### **Firestore Security Rules**

Copy and paste the following into the **Rules** tab of your Firestore Database:

```javascript
rules_version = '2';

service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Helper: Check if user is logged in
    function isSignedIn() {
      return request.auth != null;
    }

    // Helper: Check if the document belongs to the authenticated user
    function isOwner(userId) {
      return isSignedIn() && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }

    // Helper: Check if the user is an administrator
    function isAdmin() {
      return isSignedIn() && 
        get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.isAdmin == true;
    }

    // --- Users Collection ---
    match /users/{userId} {
      // Users can read their own profile; Admins can read all
      allow read: if isOwner(userId) || isAdmin();

      // Allow initial creation during registration
      allow create: if isOwner(userId) && 
                    request.resource.data.isAdmin == false &&
                    request.resource.data.capitalBalance == 0 &&
                    request.resource.data.profitBalance == 0;

      // Prevent users from changing their own balance or Admin status
      // Only Admins can update balances and status
      allow update: if isAdmin() || (
        isOwner(userId) && 
        !request.resource.data.diff(resource.data).affectedKeys()
          .hasAny(['isAdmin', 'capitalBalance', 'profitBalance', 'totalEarned', 'referralEarnings', 'welcomeBonus'])
      );
    }

    // --- Transactions Collection ---
    match /transactions/{txId} {
      // Users can read their own transactions; Admins can read all
      allow read: if isSignedIn() && (request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId || isAdmin());

      // Users can create transactions (e.g., for withdrawal requests or deposit simulation)
      // In a live app, deposit creation would be locked to a backend/webhook
      allow create: if isSignedIn() && request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;

      // Only Admins can update or delete transaction statuses
      allow update, delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- Active Packages Collection ---
    match /activePackages/{pkgId} {
      // Users can read their own active nodes; Admins can read all
      allow read: if isSignedIn() && (request.auth.uid == resource.data.userId || isAdmin());

      // Users can create their own package activation
      allow create: if isSignedIn() && request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;

      // Only Admins (or the ROI engine) can update package earnings
      allow update, delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- Global Settings (Optional) ---
    match /settings/{settingId} {
      allow read: if isSignedIn();
      allow write: if isAdmin();
    }
  }
}
```

### **Firebase Authentication Security**
Since you are using Email/Password authentication, make sure to:
1.  **Enable Email/Password Provider**: In the Firebase Console, go to **Authentication > Sign-in method** and enable "Email/Password".
2.  **Referral Logic**: Since referrals are handled client-side in your `store.ts`, the rules above ensure that even if a user tries to "fake" an update to their `referralEarnings`, the `allow update` rule will block the request because it contains a protected key.

### **Important Note on "Execute Cycle" (ROI)**
In your current setup, the **Admin Panel** triggers the ROI distribution from the browser. For this to work with the rules above, the user logged in as Admin **must** have the field `isAdmin: true` in their Firestore document in the `users` collection. 

**To set your first Admin:**
1.  Register an account normally.
2.  Go to the Firebase Console > **Firestore Database**.
3.  Find your user document and manually add/change the field `isAdmin` to `true` (Boolean).

