To ensure your application functions correctly and remains secure, you need to implement these rules in your **Firebase Console > Firestore Database > Rules** tab.

These rules account for:
1.  **Identity Protection**: Users can only see their own profiles.
2.  **Administrative Override**: Admins have global read/write access to manage the network.
3.  **Financial Integrity**: Preventing users from manually increasing their own balances.
4.  **Vault Security**: Strictly limiting hot wallet keys to administrative access only.

### Firestore Security Rules

```javascript
rules_version = '2';

service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Helper: Check if user is authenticated
    function isSignedIn() {
      return request.auth != null;
    }

    // Helper: Check if user document indicates admin status
    function isAdmin() {
      return isSignedIn() && 
        get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.isAdmin == true;
    }

    // Helper: Check if user is the owner of the document
    function isOwner(userId) {
      return isSignedIn() && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }

    // --- USERS COLLECTION ---
    match /users/{userId} {
      // Admins can see everyone; Users can only see themselves
      allow read: if isOwner(userId) || isAdmin();

      // Allow initial account creation
      allow create: if isSignedIn() && request.resource.id == request.auth.uid;

      // Update logic
      allow update: if isAdmin() || (
        isOwner(userId) && 
        // Prevent users from granting themselves Admin or changing their own balances
        request.resource.data.isAdmin == resource.data.isAdmin &&
        request.resource.data.capitalBalance == resource.data.capitalBalance &&
        request.resource.data.profitBalance == resource.data.profitBalance &&
        request.resource.data.totalEarned == resource.data.totalEarned
      );
    }

    // --- TRANSACTIONS COLLECTION ---
    match /transactions/{txId} {
      // Admins see all; Users see their own history
      allow read: if isAdmin() || (isSignedIn() && resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid);

      // Users can create a transaction (e.g., initiating a withdrawal)
      allow create: if isSignedIn() && request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;

      // Only Admins can modify status (Confirm/Reject/Authorize)
      allow update: if isAdmin();

      allow delete: if false; // Audit logs should never be deleted
    }

    // --- ACTIVE PACKAGES COLLECTION ---
    match /activePackages/{apId} {
      allow read: if isAdmin() || (isSignedIn() && resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid);

      // Users can activate a package (create)
      allow create: if isSignedIn() && request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;

      // Only Admins update these (ROI distribution)
      allow update: if isAdmin();

      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- VAULT COLLECTION (Hot Wallet Keys) ---
    match /vault/{document=**} {
      // Critical security: ONLY Admins can see or set the Hot Wallet config
      allow read, write: if isAdmin();
    }
  }
}
```

### Deployment Instructions

1.  **Firebase Console**: Go to **Build > Firestore Database**.
2.  **Rules Tab**: Click the **Rules** tab at the top.
3.  **Paste**: Delete everything currently there and paste the code above.
4.  **Publish**: Click the blue **Publish** button.

### Note on Balance Security
In the current client-side implementation (using `updateDoc` and `runTransaction` directly in `store.ts`), these rules provide the best possible protection. In a production environment with higher capital, I would recommend moving the "ROI Execution" and "Deposit Sync" logic to **Firebase Cloud Functions** (Node.js) so that secret keys (like your `TRONGRID_API_KEY`) and balance increments never happen directly on the user's browser.

